    "content": "nullReport and Reduce Your Carbon Footprint with Net Zero Cloud\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Report and Reduce Your Carbon Footprint with Net Zero Cloud\n Get Ready to Use Net Zero Cloud\n Determine the Sources to Inventory\n Emissions Factors That Affect Calculations\n Create Your Consumption Records\n Manage Scope 3 Value Chain Data\n Manage Your Carbon Footprint\n Manage Your Water Footprint\n Manage the Annual Emissions Inventory\n Record Locking and Recalculation\n Benchmark Building Energy Intensity Data\n Manage Carbon Footprint Data Gaps\n Set Emissions Targets\n Emissions Forecasting\n Carbon Accounting for Extended Organizational Boundaries\n Carbon Accounting for Partner Community Users\n Engage Suppliers for Emissions Reduction\n Allocate Carbon Credits to Offset Unavoidable Emissions\n Allocate Energy Attribute Certificate Credits to Reduce Scope 2...\n Report Social and Governance Data with Net Zero Cloud\n Create a Disclosure Reporting Period\n Summarize Employee Demographic Information\n Summarize Organization Incident Information\n Summarize Economic Performance Information\n Summarize Anti-Corruption Initiative Information\n Summarize Tax Disclosure Information\n Summarize Employment Benefit Information\n Summarize Employee Development Information\n Summarize Diversity Equity Inclusion Information\n Summarize Social Contribution Information\n Summarize Government Financial Assistance Information\n Summarize Employment Compensation Information\n Summarize Managed Care Program Performance\n Social and Governance Data for Extended Organizational Boundaries\n Social and Governance Data for Affiliates\n Materiality Assessment\n Generate Disclosures by Using Disclosure and Compliance Hub\n Data Collection\n Improve Decarbonization Strategy with Sustainability Programs\n Data Auditing\n Submit Records for Approval\n Use Net Zero Analytics App\n Use DEI Analytics App\n Report Your Carbon Footprint\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nREPORT AND REDUCE YOUR CARBON FOOTPRINT WITH NET ZERO CLOUD\nReport Social and Governance Data with Net Zero Cloud\n\nEnter, store, extract, and report quantitative disclosures in social and governance reports with reference to GRI Standards. All companies must adhere to GRI Universal Standards, but standards that apply to specific sectors and topics need to be reported only if they’re required by governing bodies.\n\nREQUIRED EDITIONS\nAvailable in: Lightning Experience\nAvailable in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions\nCreate a Disclosure Reporting Period\nCreate a disclosure reporting period for stakeholder disclosure reports.\nSummarize Employee Demographic Information\nAn employee demographic summary includes information about all employees who work for your organization.\nSummarize Organization Incident Information\nCreate a summary of incidents in your organization, such as noncompliance with laws, corruption, health and safety, discrimination, marketing and labeling, and customer privacy.\nSummarize Economic Performance Information\nA summary of the economic performance of your organization provides a basic indication of how the organization has created wealth for stakeholders.\nSummarize Anti-Corruption Initiative Information\nA summary of anti-corruption initiatives taken by your organization provides information about how the organization communicates and trains employees on anti-corruption policies and procedures.\nSummarize Tax Disclosure Information\nA summary of tax disclosures of your organization provides statistics about the disclosure of business entity information to all tax jurisdictions.\nSummarize Employment Benefit Information\nA summary of employee benefits of your organization provides statistics about benefits provided to employees and the usage of benefits.\nSummarize Employee Development Information\nA summary of employee development within an organization includes the scale of the organization’s investment in training, and the degree to which the investment is made across the entire employee base.\nSummarize Diversity Equity Inclusion Information\nA summary of diversity equity inclusion in your organization provides a quantitative measure of diversity within the organization based on the employee type, gender, age group, and other diversity indicators.\nSummarize Social Contribution Information\nA summary of social contributions by your organization includes details of the organization’s contributions in line with its stated policies, goals, or other public positions.\nSummarize Government Financial Assistance Information\nA summary of social contributions by your organization includes details of the organization’s contributions in line with its stated policies, goals, or other public positions.\nSummarize Employment Compensation Information\nCreate a summary by region of the average hourly wage and percentage of facility-based employees earning minimum wage.\nSummarize Managed Care Program Performance\nCreate a summary of the rating and enrollee retention rate according to the managed care program type, such as Medicare Advantage.\nSocial and Governance Data for Extended Organizational Boundaries\nEnter and manage social and governance data for extended organizational boundaries, such as subsidiaries of the parent company, within a single organization. You can then consolidate the data for extended organizational boundaries in the parent company’s social and governance data reports.\nSocial and Governance Data for Affiliates\nYou can give affiliates access to Net Zero Cloud objects to enter and manage their social and governance data in Net Zero Cloud through the Experience Cloud site that you create.\nMateriality Assessment\nA double materiality assessment is the first step in defining your company’s corporate social responsibility (CSR) and environment, social, and governance (ESG) strategy. When you conduct a materiality assessment, you identify the areas of risk to your business and the opportunities for making an impact on the environment and society. The assessment helps your company set an environment, social, and governance plan that’s aligned with your corporate strategy and the expectations of your company’s stakeholders.\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
